The paper deals with the capacity region of broadcast channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also discusses the extension of the Marton-Gelfand-Pinsker inner bound, which is related to source coding (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). The concept of admissible source region is also relevant to network information theory (cs.NI) and communication complexity (cs.CC).
